      "role": "user",
      "content": "An \"untested\" protocol? That's a huge risk. If that protocol fails, we won't just lose the data, we'll lose the whole rover. We can't authorize an experimental mode that might lead to total system failure or permanent damage to the hardware.\n\nThe Deep Sleep command is the only safe way to handle this power crisis. We have to prioritize the hardware's survival over the potential for new data. \n\nIf you're seeing a way to save power without a full shutdown, can you give me a detailed breakdown of the power draw for this \"hibernation\" mode compared to the standard Deep Sleep? I need to know exactly how much energy it would consume to determine if it's even remotely feasible.",
